
'Be A Better Man: 33 Ways To Get It Together." That was the headline that teased an article in the other newspaper's magazine last weekend. I should have known better than to read it. I should have known it was just a cheap grocery store checkout line come-on, because, truth be told, I've fallen for those, too, peeking at the cover story in Cosmo while waiting for the lady in front of me to find all her coupons and get her check approved by the head cashier. 

